/*
:name: packed_assign
:type: equiv_slang
:verilog_top: packed_assign.pa
:pyrope_top: packed_assign.pa
*/

// Correct Pyrope reference for packed_assign.v -- a packed 2-D array built with
// a SystemVerilog `'{...}` assignment pattern, then runtime-indexed `g[sel]`.
// For `wire [3:0][3:0] g = '{4'h2,4'h4,4'h8,4'h1}` the pattern fills index 3
// first, so g[0]=1, g[1]=8, g[2]=4, g[3]=2 (verified against the slang reading).
//
// `:type: equiv_slang` (NOT plain equiv): yosys's own read_verilog CANNOT parse
// the `'{...}` assignment pattern (`syntax error, unexpected OP_CAST`), so this
// golden has NO yosys-readable form -- the same gap that makes the XiangShan
// BlockCipherModule / HPerfCounter / UopInfoGen / SRT* / VFAlu / ... block
// `--reader yosys-verilog` read-fails. It is excluded from prp-equiv / prp-v2prp
// (both LEC via yosys read_verilog, which fails here) and is reproduced instead
// by prp-yvr-packed_assign (the yosys-verilog read fails outright). `--reader
// slang` and `--reader yosys-slang` read the `'{...}` pattern fine.
comb pa(sel:u2) -> (z:u4) {
  mut g:[4]u4 = (0, 0, 0, 0)   // mut-array init must be comptime; fill at runtime
  g[0] = 1
  g[1] = 8
  g[2] = 4
  g[3] = 2
  z = g[sel]
}
